{
  "description": "A close-up, intimate view inside a red tulip flower. The perspective is from within the blossom, looking up at the stamens and pistil. The stamens are a dark, almost black, color with yellow pollen dusting their tips. The pistil is a pale yellow-green. The inner petals are a gradient of pale yellow at the base transitioning to a vibrant, saturated red. The petals appear slightly wrinkled and soft, indicating their delicate texture. The lighting is soft and diffused, highlighting the intricate details of the floral structure. There's a shallow depth of field, which keeps the focus sharply on the stamens and pistil while blurring the surrounding petals.",
